---

# Episode 6 — Node 05 — Send Reply

## Node Info
```
Node Type : Gmail — Send Email
Node Name : 05 - Send Reply
What it does: Sends the AI written reply
              back to whoever emailed us
```

## How I Built It
```
Click "+" after Node 04
Search: Gmail
Select it (Actions — NOT Trigger)
Rename: 05 - Send Reply
Credential: My Gmail account
Operation: Send
```

## Email Config I Set Up
```
To      : {{ $json.sender_email }}
Subject : Re: {{ $json.subject }}
Message : {{ $json.reply }}
```

## Why I Built It This Way
Re: in the subject line makes it look like a real human replied.
People trust it more — feels personal and professional.
The reply field already contains the full AI written email.
Drop it in and send — no extra work needed.
The whole thing happens in seconds.
The sender has no idea it was written by AI.

---

---

# Episode 7 — Node 06 — Log to Sheet

## Node Info
```
Node Type : Google Sheets — Append Row
Node Name : 06 - Log to Sheet
What it does: Saves every email and AI reply
              to Google Sheets for full tracking
```

## How I Built It
```
Click "+" after Node 05
Search: Google Sheets
Select it
Rename: 06 - Log to Sheet
Operation: Append Row
Document: Workflow 10 - Email Auto Responder
Sheet: Sheet1
Mapping: Map Each Column Manually
```

## Column Mapping I Set Up
```
Timestamp    → {{ $now.toISO() }}
Sender Name  → {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.sender_name }}
Sender Email → {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.sender_email }}
Subject      → {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.subject }}
Email Body   → {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.body }}
AI Reply     → {{ $('04 - Parse AI Response').item.json.reply }}
Status       → Replied
```

## Why I Built It This Way
This log is the most valuable thing for the client.
Every email, every reply, every timestamp — all in one place.
Nothing gets lost. Nothing gets forgotten.
Status is hardcoded as Replied because by the time
this node runs, the reply has already been sent.
Client can filter by category, date, sender — full visibility.
This is what turns a $200 setup into a $500 setup.

---

---

# All Lessons I Learned

```
Lesson 1 — Gmail Trigger Location
In n8n 2026, Gmail Trigger is under:
Gmail → Triggers section → On message received ⚡
Not in the main search as a separate node.

Lesson 2 — Email Body Field
$json.text sometimes returns empty.
Use $json.snippet instead.
snippet is always available — it is Gmail's preview text.

Lesson 3 — Same OpenAI Path as Workflow 9
output[0].content[0].text ✅
This is the standard path for all OpenAI nodes in n8n 2026.
Memorize it — use it in every workflow.

Lesson 4 — Re: In Subject Line
Putting Re: before the subject makes replies
look like real human responses.
Clients and their customers trust it more.
Small detail — big impact.

Lesson 5 — Category Field in AI Prompt
Asking AI to return a category alongside the reply
gives the client business intelligence for free.
They can see which type of inquiry comes most often.
This is a feature — not just a log.

Lesson 6 — System Prompt Templates
Giving AI exact reply templates for each email type
keeps the brand voice consistent every single time.
No two replies sound different.
The client never has to worry about what AI will say.
```

